Rewrite the following recursive `factorial` function in continuation-passing style (CPS). In CPS, functions never return; instead they call a continuation `k` with the value they would have returned.

Here is the original factorial:
```
var factorial = function(n) {
  if (n == 0) {
    return 1;
  } else {
    return factorial(n-1) * n;
  }
}
```

